name: Café de Grancy
reviews:
[{"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Chan Min Kang, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113043299480367429145/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTkyfcFMNW_NXI7l9hnfryMyURQ5ri1Jy3tXRjKYqSs_zYQmI=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4}","text":"Here for dinner supper. Thank you for the good service! Although the menu in French, we're super happy with this waitress that explains and introduce to us in English, wonderful! We got the seasoned salmon and vege tartare. And the creme brulee is superb!
1. Food is superb, they served them quite fast, but all are tasty!
2. Atmosphere is great inside, but outside is fully taken on a sunny day.
Will probably come back again for the brunch and great services!","rating":5}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Julie KT, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111383893551758339180/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWR5UTYvjf906Qy_D-4MtWJOuXYCjWslpiQuttLwPl6VmE5-LCj=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4}","text":"Great menu with locally sourced products. Vegetarian and vegan options available. I’ve been here a few times now and it’s always been a delight.","rating":5}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Fan Zhang, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117180237359879865202/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUNzu5b9cWxpwo0ZonJ8vmqawaclCMLTyg5UiObfNYIyFvrmFBM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5}","text":"I visited this place 2 years ago. It was nice. Today I visited again and ordered the same omelette. However the food quality is not as good as before. The omelette is too salty.","rating":3}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Farhad Munshi, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105189259903768229032/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbe4V8gmjoMTX09k5oANeHiU1jeFoXoc3InSCj3SYblPEKt7d-0A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4}","text":"Lovely outdoor seating with nice views of the lake. Expect a wait if you want to sit outside and don’t have a reservation. Interesting indoor details. Menu is in French so keep your phones translation app handy. Friendly but very busy staff with some English spoken. Flavorful dishes. Got the sausage with mustard, mashed potatoes and veggies and liked it. Large portions. Reasonably priced wine.","rating":5}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Derek Zhuang, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114131685889554644704/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZH-T9tLvbkaXc4hTbAqyWgc6E5P2UYTTVb9yCx6y56XaaO4o=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo}","text":"Have stayed in Lausanne for a week. This is by far the most expensive yet mediocre place we’ve been to. The dish is too simple and bland to justify the price of 30-40 CHF. Food ingredients are of average quality. Service is not very responsive but reasonable.","rating":2}]

name: COFFEE PAGE
reviews:
[{"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Kasey McKinney, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108460080605609779083/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZ_vvo-kZaZG4XSpMGA1d34_qBr6mjs5YfmoekdIYhYdy_tZvKPg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5}","text":"Beautiful space with friendly baristas, well balanced espresso, and iced drinks! There were many people there on a Friday morning, but it didn’t take long to get our drinks for take away. Would be a great space to sit and work for a little while or visit with friends. Indoor and outdoor seating available.","rating":5}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Emilie Malek, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106478750236679603143/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIQ9MpQXPTCv5bMg6FEbwdHAFn4SGbD5BsTeX82bUatu1Ycvw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2}","text":"My favourite café in Lausanne- coffee always on point, great service and really peaceful and cosy vibes. Also love the terrasse seating","rating":5}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Mari Matsuzaki, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106429839716188488836/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKD1fCwnBjILTvHvgJVCOdVtsAZnaB867HFSEFsrBprJquq2_0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4}","text":"A really lovely cafe where you want to go and meet with your friends. We didn't order food so we cannot speak for that, but really loved the drink options they had.
Since I was quite thirsty and needed something with ice, they kindly offered espresso tonic which was not on the menu.

All of the seats outside were packed so we sat inside, really loved the indoor space design, too!","rating":5}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Helene Lydia, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117349741063768558058/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6GPbzN2WryoaJjyUp_kp-w6Sparv-K2BlIYA0eNBcWUjITsa8gQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4}","text":"Seems to be a popular place to go for Sunday morning coffee, it was 10 AM on Sunday morning and people were already there. At that day they served the coffee at the second store (just beside the main shop), but it also had very relaxing interior with the diverse chairs/table design. There were some croissants offered (plain and jambon) if you fancy some viennoiseries. Place was nice, coffee was good, but more on the pricey side. :)","rating":5}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Matteo (matt_patt), uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109548522110877417585/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKOeME1bDZ_N6KGsTp4-2uhwUpudT0gy6nwJPOpPsYHSkR6Lg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2}","text":"Specialty coffee lovers, steer clear. They market themselves as a specialty coffee place but it’s really not. The beans are just average, they don’t know how to make a flat white (overextracted and served in a tall glass with way too much milk) and they don’t even have filter coffee. Decent but overpriced croissants, coffee way too expensive for what you get (6.50 for a flat white). The place is nice and cosy but it’s not worth it. Save yourself some disappointment and go to Bel-Air coffee instead: for the same price you get amazing beans from world-class roasters. If you want a cheaper and loftier café, but still with good coffee, Ça Passe Crème is also a great option.","rating":2}]

Additionally, the service was rather slow, and both the restrooms and the kitchen could benefit from more thorough cleaning.","rating":1}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Kat M, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100554788584202117259/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZGijC3xl0hl0xtvn5kSCAuccyqGbmw1x9hsiCCzxpFUWxyBWC=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4}","text":"The worst MacDo i ever seen in terms of personnel and clean. I believe it is a misleading management approach.
There is a dark skin woman that enters your space and tries to provoke you whenever you enter or try to make an order. when the worker accepts the wrong order that dark woman comes to make a scandalized show. that person is so disrespectful and arrogant, she should not work Anywhere to serve people. She constantly looks for ways to shoot ppl or argue with them. It happened to us three times with her presence. We stopped to go there after it since she continues to work there and management did nothing about it.
It was a good place to sip a coffee while u wait for your train but if it gives u such stress it is better to avoid it. At least until personal with a behavior like this work there, so please let us all know about it. There is only one nice and kind worker from Asia, she is smiling and doing her best no matter what task she is doing. She deserves to be a manager of this place.","rating":1}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Björn Roger Felgner, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104124702884834309118/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJn8JvlQYNdsYwwx7466kCS7kj7BBx-i9oyuNm8q3krrclSd194=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5}","text":"Nice McDonald's Restaurant right in front of the train station "Gare de Lausanne". Pretty nice to pick up something to eat before or after a train journey. The store is clean including the toilets and it didn't took long till I got my food.","rating":5}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Rea Waltová, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105709868810357722675/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUT_J7OyBTsIA59xIQe7Rdf6LttFAX7haDFcVAlUa20oQZKGRCjsw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2}","text":"This restaurant is obviously at a popular location (big fluctuations), yet it still managed to dissapoint us with its cleanliness. Especially the toilets were in absolutely horrible condition.
Personal was luckily really friendly and cleaned at least our table for us when asked.","rating":3}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Vinoth Radha, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107948904770289694958/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJ2HmyMEk1hJnECg6jTDppMmq9Ecl-xcNfiA5z5NLhKlXHLAG-=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4}","text":"Dirty tables, and chairs. Everywhere food and fries. I ordered spicy nuggets and strawberry frappé(later). Was sitting upstairs and took 20 as my table sign. Got the chicken nuggets but never the frappe, asked the waitress and she told me that she will bring me. But no. Next time I asked and she said go and ask in the counter, but I didn't have time, so left.","rating":2}]

Very friendly staff and prices are normal .","rating":5}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Arthur Bajeux, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112516942053093464780/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXD4tMuqKZkR1R_ayKXSBIv4-cMrfK75f77gX3ZbrYNQ3PbBOU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2}","text":"Excellent variety and presentation + ∞ points for 2 free donuts given on our arrival ( they might not give you one tho just 🤞) and the staff were super friendly. name: L'Académie Café | Brotherfields. & Sister | Specialty coffee
reviews:
[{"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Gino Laios, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107615250001966710872/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUw3TKwD8iHkqTgVgjdzLHn9daP4l61qX7ZHRpaXNwHK1oVs-LH=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4}","text":"A Hidden Gem in Lausanne's Historic Heart

L'Académie Café is an absolute treasure nestled in the picturesque streets of La Cité, Lausanne. This cozy café effortlessly blends vintage charm with a modern vibe, creating an inviting space perfect for a relaxed coffee break or a productive morning. From the moment you step inside, the warm, rustic decor—complete with Swiss blankets, terracotta pots, and exposed brick—makes you feel at home.

The specialty coffee here is simply outstanding, with every cup brewed to perfection. Whether you're a fan of a smooth flat white, a refreshing iced latte, or something more unique like their matcha or chai, you'll find something to love. The food menu, though thoughtfully curated, offers delightful options like avocado toast, pancakes, and tartines that pair perfectly with your beverage of choice.

What truly sets L'Académie Café apart is its welcoming atmosphere. It's an ideal spot to unwind, meet friends, or get some work done while soaking in the beautiful surroundings. Plus, the friendly and attentive staff make every visit a pleasure. If you're ever in Lausanne, this café is a must-visit for its top-notch coffee, delicious bites, and charming ambiance.","rating":5}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Rachel, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107082680250797811216/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtAS8YSvgrQN9aV3xqmPwbQjBbTEZM2onRo87XYUe1zSxsPfmrkw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4}","text":"Lovely little cafe near the Lausanne cathedral. reviews: [{"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Paula, uri=https:\/\/www.google.com\/maps\/contrib\/103703768780680870655\/reviews, photoUri=https:\/\/lh3.googleusercontent.com\/a-\/ALV-UjV2BX_e1qyIChJ6AEc2MTZsencJvMktzR-AMJBisZ9pPwVNs4uTBg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5}","text":"The best pizza in Lausanne. name: Hungry Bear | Kitchen + Coffee
reviews:
[{"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Aimee Clatterbuck, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106454451811643249974/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIgIJE9LTe5OhOFLW-ScarELfHB2etr33oEhfVg-nqE2A6nTQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo}","text":"Lovely space near the Lausanne gate station. There is indoor and outdoor dining. Best to make a reservation-yet note once the reservation has been made you have only an hour and a half at your table. Coffee was good but the food was inadequate as I got the eggplant toast and requested twice that no ham be placed on it. However, when it arrived there was ham! It was quickly removed but I was left with one thin slice of eggplant, on toast and nothing else. There are little to no vegan options on the menu. The service was slow and the food too expensive for what we paid. Would not go back again -","rating":3}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=AEM, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103095513250218469276/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIHNEd6nFtFpdWWPPL5--_zbAgz4DWD_xKMlUTfLQU5UkQLlA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4}","text":"Delicious food where you discover tastes that you did not even know it existed. Local food with a lot of flavors.
The service is very friendly and caring.
It feels like home and the ambiente is very coasy with the opportunity to sit also outside.","rating":5}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Costanza Volpini, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112750375262132765910/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXWFern8x3bZc1W0qu3BpK354AKt9boX33pgtTVZSM8zrC026o3JQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5}","text":"It's a very nice spot for brunch, though the service is a bit slow and the prices are slightly above the Lausanne average. The salmon toast was exceptional, as was the cappuccino. I was a bit disappointed by the desserts. Overall, I recommend it for those with celiac disease as they are very careful about cross-contamination.","rating":4}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Brianna Johnson, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101137866220801739611/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVZzW83JdvNtYj2Ze9Ay5LABclb9Tle0qxNEm2FICtZ_Q01HuT=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo}","text":"My boyfriend and I have been traveling and stopped in here for brunch right after visiting Sleepy Bear (right next door to Hungry Bear / a specialized coffee shop counterpart). We ordered the avocado toast with salmon and it was super fresh, high quality, and delicious! Our server was also incredibly kind and thoughtful- we had a great conversation with him.
Thank you, Hungry Bear!","rating":5}, {"authorName":"AuthorAttribution{name=Ludmila Hrižanovska, uri=https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108473441043355379549/reviews, photoUri=https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVX7PqmqWZDU-YZu3F-1ek3xI6N2-Sm4h84qu1RPZ_5Phtu7GjRTg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5}","text":"Lovely place with a good location in Lausanne. Friendly and nice service, very tasty food and interesting flavor combinations - chocolate-porcini mousse even if not my cup of tea, it us definitely a unique dessert to try, perfect for umami lovers.","rating":5}]
